b8519c77-eb94-4304-a15d-ca39c815f52a	5021-173	DMM Phantom Screwgate Carabiner	The lightest keylock locking carabiner in the world (circa spring 2010). They're light, so you can bring some extras. For the size, this carabiner has strong open gate and cross-load breaking strength. The tradeoff is overall strength and durability, which won’t be as great over the life of the carabiner.I-beam construction gives it a very impressive gate-face test of 4kN. This test pushes the gate face inward while locked.Constructed from hot-forged aluminum.	["Home", "All", "Climbing", "Rock climbing", "Carabiners and draws", "Locking carabiners", "Phantom Screwgate Carabiner"]	{"Weight": ["42g"], "Made in": ["United Kingdom"], "Material": ["Aluminum alloy"], "Gate type": ["Straight"], "Ideal for": ["Snow and ice climbing", "Rock climbing", "Indoor climbing"], "CE certified": ["Yes"], "Gate opening": ["1.6cm"], "Strength open": ["9kN"], "Strength closed": ["24kN"], "Three sigma tested": ["Yes"], "Strength cross-loaded": ["9kN"], "Lock type\\n\\nAuto-locking biners use a spring mechanism to close. Screwgate have a collar that you screw open or closed.": ["Screwgate"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807123779614/5021173-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807123779614/5021173-NOC02.jpg"]}	164.6	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5021-173/Phantom-Screwgate-Carabiner
