0001c09d-dd90-43d3-9002-c52b2a42196c	5026-510	Falcon How to Climb 5.12 3rd Edition	Enter the magic realm of 5.12 climbing. Looked upon as entry point to elite-level climbing, many intermediate climbers believe 5.12 to be out of reach. This performance manual dispels the myth, and teaches average climbers to achieve the previously exclusive domain of full-time climbers. Discover how to make the physical and mental jump to advanced climbing, through tips and suggestions for strength training, mental training and climbing strategy. The guide includes a self-assessment test to optimize your training, techniques and drills for accelerated learning of climbing skills, exercises for building strength and endurance, strategies for managing fear and building confidence, and tactics for on-sight climbing and working redpoints.	["Home", "All", "Travel gear", "Books and maps", "Training guides and instructional books", "How to Climb 5.12 3rd Edition"]	{"ISBN": ["9780762770298"], "Pages": ["176"], "Author": ["Eric J. Horst"], "Edition": ["3rd"], "Made in": ["China"], "Language": ["English"], "Ideal for": ["Climbing training", "Rock climbing"], "Published": ["2011"], "Illustrator": ["Sean Michael"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815733833758/5026510-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815733833758/5026510-NOC02.jpg"]}	145.34	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5026-510/How-to-Climb-5-12-3rd-Edition
51962c5a-bd2c-410f-83e0-b4a3378b6d97	5025-300	Falcon How to Climb: Self-Rescue 2nd Edition	Whether you need to assist your partner past a difficult section, or rappel down a multipitch route with an injured climber, you owe it to yourself and your fellow climbers to be prepared. Self-Rescue fully describes and illustrates techniques that every climber needs to know for safety and self-reliance. Revised with the latest techniques and accompanied by Mike Clelland's clear illustrations, this is the definitive resource on the topic. It includes self-rescue concepts: terrain, technical ledges, baseline and belay escapes, knots and hitches, anchors and belays, assessment of patients and terrain, top-rope rescue, leader rescue, and search and rescue.	["Home", "All", "Travel gear", "Books and maps", "Training guides and instructional books", "How to Climb: Self-Rescue 2nd Edition"]	{"ISBN": ["9780762755332"], "Pages": ["246"], "Author": ["David Fasulo"], "Edition": ["2nd"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Language": ["English"], "Ideal for": ["Rock climbing", "Climbing training"], "Published": ["2011"], "Illustrator": ["Mike Clelland"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815729934366/5025300-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815729934366/5025300-NOC02.jpg"]}	151.08	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5025-300/How-to-Climb%3A-Self-Rescue-2nd-Edition
