627319a3-9b9d-44eb-9acc-80e67e850741	5026-548	Garmin eTrex 10 GPS	Maybe you navigate with map and compass, but there have been times when you weren’t absolutely sure of your way back to the trailhead. Carry the eTrex 10 as an ace up your sleeve for those situations. Enter the car or camp as a waypoint and your GPS will point you to your destination. Leave it running while you’re on the move and use the TrackBack® feature to retrace your path back turn by turn.Simple, affordable device, great for geocaching.High-sensitivity, WAAS-enabled GPS receiver.HotFix® satellite prediction for quick acquisition and good signal lock, even through heavy cover, deep canyons, and tall buildings.Four level grey display.Built-in worldwide basemap.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Electronics", "GPS Navigation", "Handheld GPS", "eTrex 10 GPS"]	{"Floats": ["No"], "Routes": ["50"], "Weight": ["141g"], "Made in": ["Taiwan"], "Batteries": ["2 AA (not included)"], "Bluetooth": ["No"], "Data card": ["Not accepted"], "Ideal for": ["Alpine climbing and mountaineering", "Backcountry skiing"], "Interface": ["USB"], "Track log": ["10,000 points, 100 saved tracks"], "Dimensions": ["10.3 x 5.4 x 3.3cm"], "Chest strap": ["Not compatible"], "Tide tables": ["No"], "Battery life": ["25 h"], "Touch screen": ["No"], "Haptic feedback": ["No"], "Area calculation": ["Yes"], "Display dimensions": ["4.4 x 3.5cm"], "Unit to unit transfer\\n\\nShares data wirelessly between compatible units.": ["No"], "App compatibility\\n\\nAn online community where members upload, analyze and share activity data.": ["None"], "Basemap\\n\\nA basic set of map data that is included with the GPS. Basemap detail may vary from unit to unit.": ["Yes"], "Add maps capability\\n\\nThese units allow you to add maps, so you can mark and name waypoints and create routes on your PC, and then upload the map of your choice to your GPS.": ["No"], "Electronic compass\\n\\nAn electronic compass allows the user to view their heading in situations where they are either standing still or moving too slowly for the GPS to detect.": ["No"], "Barometric altimeter\\n\\nBarometer function helps forecast weather trends. An altimeter can provide one line of position for location on a topo map, useful if the GPS isn't working.": ["No"], "Waypoints\\n\\nWaypoints consist of a standard set of coordinates (two for land, three for air or space) that identify a specific physical location. A route is navigated between two or more waypoints.": ["1000"], "Custom POI\\n\\nA POI (point of interest) is a specific location that someone may find interesting (i.e., favourite viewpoint, best coffee stop before the trailhead). The custom POI feature allows the user to load only the POI's that interest them onto their GPS unit.": ["Yes"], "IPX rating\\n\\nIndicates the degree of protection against liquid. IP X1: Dripping water while in normal operating orientation; IP X4: Splashing water; IP X5: Water jets; IP X6: Powerful water jets; IP X7: Immersion up to 1m ≤ 30 minutes; IP X8: Suitable for submersion as specified by manufacturer.": ["IP X7"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8810569039902/5026548-YLW00.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8810569039902/5026548-YLW00.jpg"]}	143.43	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5026-548/eTrex-10-GPS
