eebbbc45-0714-4a1a-9c1c-16fd8e0bd7b2	5022-762	MEC Stratosphere Crew - Youths	This warm, lightweight fleece can be worn year-round as a mid-layer, pulled on over a T-shirt, or as a base layer through the winter. The fabric moves moisture, so it's comfortable through a range of activities and assorted atmospheric conditions.Made from soft, moisture-wicking 100% polyester fleece.Flat-locked seams eliminate friction under backpack straps.Stretchy neck opening for easy dressing.Raglan sleeves for extra mobility.Coordinates with MEC Stratosphere Tights.\n\nRegular fit\n\n\n\nFit guide\n\nTechnical garments, designed for specific activities have features that aren’t always adaptable to general use. For example, cycling clothing is longer in the back and arms. Activity aside, the fit of MEC clothing falls into these categories:\n\n\n\n\n\nTight, with no room to spare.\n\n\n\n\n\nVery close fit, with a bit of room.\n\n\n\n\n\nGenerous, but not oversized.\n\n\n\n\n\nOversized with lots of room for layers.\n\n\nAll MEC men’s and boy’s pants are regular rise.\n\n\n\n\n        Sustainability\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBluesign\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n                      Bluesign® Approved Material	["Home", "All", "Kids", "Youth (8-16 yrs)", "Youth clothing", "Youth t-shirts and tops", "Youth long sleeved t-shirts", "Stratosphere Crew"]	{"Type": ["Mid-layer", "Fleece"], "Weight": ["99g (Youth 8)"], "Made in": ["El Salvador"], "Ideal for": ["Casual wear", "Downhill skiing", "Snowboarding"], "Fabric content": ["100% polyester"], "Product sustainability": ["Bluesign® Approved Material"], "Durable water repellency\\n\\nUsually referred to as DWR. A treatment made to fabrics that causes water to bead and run off instead of soaking through.": ["No"], "Windproofness\\n\\nA windproof garment does not allow any air to permeate the fabric.  A garment with windproof panels has panels of fabric that are totally windproof, but the rest of the garment may not be windproof.  A wind-resistant garment res