-ALT-ALLSIZES.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9049623199774/5015640-NOC02-ALT-TOP.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9049610321950/5015640-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9049623035934/5015640-NOC02-ALT-ALLSIZESBACK.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9049623232542/5015640-NOC02-ALT-ALLSIZES.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9049623199774/5015640-NOC02-ALT-TOP.jpg"]}	91.61	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5015-640/Fuel-Bottle
b1c342a6-d52b-4fde-957f-c92223a4bb7b	1699-628	MSR Heat Exchanger Unit	An engineered cooking accessory for improving fuel economy while melting snow or boiling water on longer trips. Not recommended for delicate cooking or simmering, since any spillage will be difficult to clean out of the unit.Compatible with all MSR® 1.5L and 2L pots (with the exception of the Titan™ 1.5L and Trail Lite Duo Pot).Corrugated surface channels additional stove heat into the pot through the sides.The unit can improve heat transfer, and fuel consumption, by up to 25%.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Outdoor cookware", "Pots and pot sets", "Pot handles, grippers and accessories", "Heat Exchanger Unit"]	{"Weight": ["160g"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Backpacking", "Winter and expedition camping"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812745359390/1699628-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812745359390/1699628-NOC02.jpg"]}	40.12	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/1699-628/Heat-Exchanger-Unit
fd82a35d-dd18-405f-96ea-7e548723ba6f	5015-631	MSR HyperFlow Microfilter	Filter water faster with minimal pumping effort. This lightweight, ultra-compact, high-flow system filters down to 0.2 micron, removing 99.99% of all bacteria and protozoa. The output is a considerable 2.75L of water per minute.Hollow fibre technology uses proprietary polymer fibres to create a high surface-area filter that allows water to flow quickly through a 0.2 micron effective pore size.A quick-connect adapter attaches the filter to any bottle or reservoir with a standard 63mm threaded opening.The polycarbonate filter body is tough, compact and light in weight.Silicon input hose with pre-filter.Field maintainable, can be easily reconfigured to allow backflushing for flow recovery. No tools required for complete disassembly.Note: These fibres are slightly more brittle than other filter materials and somewhat more susceptible to damage from strong impact. Although the cartridge is protected by the polycarbonate pump body and has been drop-tested to three feet, you should consider carrying a spare cartridge on long trips – they are small, light, and relatively inexpensive. Do not allow the cartridge to freeze after initial use.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Water bottles and water treatment", "Water filters, treatment and tablets", "Water filters", "Pump filters", "HyperFlow Microfilter"]	{"Output": ["3L/min"], "Weight": ["221g"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking"], "Dimensions": ["17.8 x 8.3cm"], "Effective against particulate\\n\\nParticulate consists of very small bits and pieces such as dirt or bugs.": ["Yes"], "Effective against protozoa\\n\\nProtozoa are larger than one micron and include cryptosporidium and giardia.": ["Yes"], "Effective against viruses\\n\\nMost viruses are in the 0.1 micron size range, but they can be as small as 0.002 microns.": ["No"], "Filter size\\n\\nA 0.5 micron or smaller filters protozoa and some large bacteria; 0.2 micron or smaller filters smaller bacteria such as campylobacter.": ["0.2microns"], "Effective against bacteria\\n\\nBacteria can cause illnesses such as diarrhea and dysentery and are about 1.0 micron in size, although some can be as small as 0.2 microns.": ["Yes"], "Filter type\\n\\nWater can be treated using various types of filters, chemicals or non-chemical purification methods, or a combination. Filters on their own will not remove viruses as they are too small.": ["Hollow fibre technology"], "Cartridge life\\n\\nThe life of the filter cartridge is based on the quantity of water you can treat before the cartridge is no longer effective. This does not apply to battery operated or chemical filter systems.": ["1000L"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812678119454/5015631-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812678119454/5015631-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812678119454/5015631-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812678119454/5015631-NOC02.jpg"]}	23.09	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5015-631/HyperFlow-Microfilter
a9d8493a-039f-47fe-a508-dab82ae8da32	4014-873	MSR Isopro 227 Fuel Canister	For use with MSR® canister stoves, the fuel is clean-burning, 80/20 blend of Isobutane and propane.  The short, wide canister provides good stability on uneven surfaces.Fuel maintains pressure from 55psi per gram down to 30psi per gram, so it functions well even as the canister empties.Self-sealing Lindal valve.Contains 227g of fuel.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Stoves, fuel and fire", "Fuel", "Isopro 227 Fuel Canister"]	{"Weight": ["377g"], "Made in": ["Korea, Republic of"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking"], "Shelf life (opened)": ["60mo"], "Shelf life (sealed)": ["60mo"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8859962114078/4014873-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8859962114078/4014873-NOC02.jpg"]}	88.33	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/4014-873/Isopro-227-Fuel-Canister
9ecb85cd-1996-42cc-b903-68a695296413	5001-239	MSR MiniWorks EX Water Filter	The MSR® Miniworks™ EX water filter is lightweight, with the same easy pumping action and carbon-cored ceramic element as the MSR WaterWorks™ EX filter, but without the final membrane filter. The side-mounted lever is easier to use than bike-pump-type filters. The base of the filter is threaded to screw directly onto Nalgene® wide-mouth water bottles or all MSR Dromedary™ bags, reducing spillage and the risk of cross-contamination with unfiltered water. The over-pressure relief valve vents water back down the intake hose, so you don’t get soaked with untreated water. A gauge is supplied so you can determine when it’s time to replace the ceramic filter element.Filters at 1L per minute flow rate using AirSpring™ air bubble technology.Effective against protozoa, and 0.2 micron or larger bacteria.Reduces concentrations of some chemicals (including iodine and chlorine).Reduces odours and tastes.Foam pre-filter included.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Water bottles and water treatment", "Water filters, treatment and tablets", "Water filters", "Pump filters", "MiniWorks EX Water Filter"]	{"Output": ["1L/min"], "Weight": ["456g"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking"], "Dimensions": ["19 x 7cm"], "Effective against particulate\\n\\nParticulate consists of very small bits and pieces such as dirt or bugs.": ["Yes"], "Effective against protozoa\\n\\nProtozoa are larger than one micron and include cryptosporidium and giardia.": ["Yes"], "Effective against viruses\\n\\nMost viruses are in the 0.1 micron size range, but they can be as small as 0.002 microns.": ["No"], "Filter size\\n\\nA 0.5 micron or smaller filters protozoa and some large bacteria; 0.2 micron or smaller filters smaller bacteria such as campylobacter.": ["0.2microns"], "Effective against bacteria\\n\\nBacteria can cause illnesses such as diarrhea and dysentery and are about 1.0 micron in size, although some can be as small as 0.2 microns.": ["Yes"], "Filter type\\n\\nWater can be treated using various types of filters, chemicals or non-chemical purification methods, or a combination. Filters on their own will not remove viruses as they are too small.": ["Ceramic filter w/carbon core"], "Cartridge life\\n\\nThe life of the filter cartridge is based on the quantity of water you can treat before the cartridge is no longer effective. This does not apply to battery operated or chemical filter systems.": ["2000L"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812675498014/5001239-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812675498014/5001239-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812675498014/5001239-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812675498014/5001239-NOC02.jpg"]}	58.47	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5001-239/MiniWorks-EX-Water-Filter
fd3196b4-731e-4678-90fd-cdd4872464cb	4008-952	MSR PanHandler Potlifter	Backpackers who begrudge every gram in their packs will appreciate the fact that the Panhandler is full of holes. These holes lighten the implement and give your hands a surer grip on it, without compromising its strength.Made of aluminum.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Outdoor cookware", "Pots and pot sets", "Pot handles, grippers and accessories", "PanHandler Potlifter"]	{"Weight": ["30g"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812723666974/4008952-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812723666974/4008952-NOC02.jpg"]}	44.71	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/4008-952/PanHandler-Potlifter
497cc530-87d6-4051-8ea9-384a5a670b95	5013-029	MSR Reactor 1.7L Stove System	Fast, fuel efficient, and virtually windproof, this stove system performs well in tough conditions. The stove has an integrated windscreen and a radiant burner with zero clearance between it and the pot. This minimizes heat loss and provides a stable flame. The heat exchanger is integrated into the cooking pot, so it's designed to be used as a system, and doesn't support standard flat-bottomed pots.1.7L pot is made of hard anodized aluminum.Burns for about 80 minutes and boils 22L of water with a 227g canister.Produces consistent heat output. The burner operates near max at lower fuel pressures and improves output in colder temperatures. An internal regulator equalizes pressure for consistent boil times throughout the life of a canister.Stove and the canister fit into the pot for travel, and a locking lid keeps it all secure.Operates to -15°C.Uses MSR LPG canisters (available separately).	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Camping kitchen and hydration", "Stoves, fuel and fire", "Camp stoves and grills", "Backcountry stoves", "Canister stoves", "Reactor 1.7L Stove System"]	{"Weight": ["496g"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Simmers": ["No"], "Ideal for": ["Backpacking"], "Dimensions": ["15.5 x 19cm"], "Windscreen": ["Yes"], "Pot included": ["Yes"], "Piezo ignition": ["No"], "Burner components": ["Magnesium", "Steel", "Aluminum"], "Fuel pump\\n\\nLiquid fuel stoves require a fuel pump to pressurize the fuel tank.": ["No"], "Fuel\\n\\nStoves are designed to burn specific fuels. All stoves should only be used with recommended fuels to prevent damage.": ["LPG"], "Boil time\\n\\nThe average time it takes to boil 1L of water. Wind, air temperature and elevation will affect boil time in the field.": ["3-3.5 min"], "Heat reflector\\n\\nHeat reflectors are placed under the burner and reflect heat back up towards the cooking pot. This helps save fuel and speed cooking time.": ["No"], "Output\\n\\nThe output of any heat generating device is shown in BTUs (British Thermal Units) which measure the amount of heat energy needed to raise the temperature of 1lb. of water by 1°F.": ["9000BTU"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643090462/5013029-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643123230/5013029-NOC02-ALT-PACKED.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643319838/5013029-NOC02-ALT-LIDCLOSED.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643647518/5013029-NOC02-ALT-XRAY.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643090462/5013029-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643123230/5013029-NOC02-ALT-PACKED.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643319838/5013029-NOC02-ALT-LIDCLOSED.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643647518/5013029-NOC02-ALT-XRAY.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643090462/5013029-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643123230/5013029-NOC02-ALT-PACKED.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643319838/5013029-NOC02-ALT-LIDCLOSED.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643647518/5013029-NOC02-ALT-XRAY.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643090462/5013029-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643123230/5013029-NOC02-ALT-PACKED.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643319838/5013029-NOC02-ALT-LIDCLOSED.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8812643647518/5013029-NOC02-ALT-XRAY.jpg"]}	105.45	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5013-029/Reactor-1-7L-Stove-System
