6e9936b3-d338-4a44-b6f5-cc716bb414d1	5022-757	Merrell Thermo Arc II 8 Waterproof Winter Boots - Women's	Tramping the well trodden paths on winter hikes. Floating across freshly fallen powder on your snowshoes. Enjoying a restorative hot chocolate at the ski chalet when the day is done. These boots are good for all that, and more. They’re warm, supportive, stylish, and built with women’s-specific lasts and midsole designs.Uppers are waterproof nubuck, with polyester mesh bellow tongues.Waterproof TPU lower shells.Polartec® 200 lining with Aegis® antimicrobial treatment, for next-to-foot comfort and odour reduction. Faux fur collar.PrimaLoft® insulation is warm, even if wet.TPU backstay with snowshoe binding strap ridges.Ortholite™ insulating footbeds.Midsoles are triple-density, compression-moulded EVA, with women's specific footframes.Tapered nylon insoles moulded to bottom of foot-frames.Outsoles are winter-specific Vibram® thermo rubber, with 6.5mm lugs.Active temperature rating is -40°C.	["Home", "All", "Footwear", "Boots", "Winter boots", "Active winter boots", "Thermo Arc II 8 Waterproof Winter Boots"]	{"Closure": ["Lace-up"], "Made in": ["Vietnam"], "Ideal for": ["Active winter wear"], "Insulation": ["400g synthetic insulation"], "Upper material": ["Nubuck leather"], "Lining material": ["Fleece"], "Removable inner boot": ["No"], "Height\\n\\nThe approximate boot height for the average person.": ["Above ankle"], "Waterproof\\n\\nWaterproof shoes and boots feature a waterproof-breathable membrane and a gusseted tongue to help keep your feet dry in wet conditions.": ["Yes"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063841595422/5022757-BK000.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842021406/5022757-BK000-ALT-MEDIAL.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842086942/5022757-BK000-ALT-LATERAL.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842250782/5022757-BK000-ALT-TOE.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063841595422/5022757-BK000.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842021406/5022757-BK000-ALT-MEDIAL.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842086942/5022757-BK000-ALT-LATERAL.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842250782/5022757-BK000-ALT-TOE.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063841595422/5022757-BK000.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842021406/5022757-BK000-ALT-MEDIAL.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842086942/5022757-BK000-ALT-LATERAL.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842250782/5022757-BK000-ALT-TOE.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063841595422/5022757-BK000.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842021406/5022757-BK000-ALT-MEDIAL.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842086942/5022757-BK000-ALT-LATERAL.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/9063842250782/5022757-BK000-ALT-TOE.jpg"]}	221.18	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5022-757/Thermo-Arc-II-8-Waterproof-Winter-Boots
2373b6a3-80c7-4071-9d10-330eb8845419	4015-348	Metolius Adjustable Aider	Using an ingenious buckle system, these aiders have a single step but are infinitely adjustable. The aider’s length is locked in place under load via 2 cam buckles that lock onto the webbing. No more messy multi-step set-ups or moving in and out to adjust your reach. Some climbers may still prefer the stepped versions to avoid constant adjusting.Sold individually, left or right.Broad support step with fastening buckle.Single-hand length adjustment via thumb loop.Carabiner must be fed through tight webbing loop, not just adjusting loop (it will slip).Less bulky and cumbersome than stepped aiders.	["Home", "All", "Climbing", "Rock climbing", "Rock hardware", "Aid climbing gear", "Adjustable Aider"]	{"Steps": ["1"], "Width": ["19mm"], "Weight": ["215g (Left)"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Aid climbing"], "Overall length": ["238cm"], "Cheater rung(s)": ["No"], "Step stiffeners": ["Yes"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807304069150/4015348-NOC00.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807304069150/4015348-NOC00.jpg"]}	116.69	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/4015-348/Adjustable-Aider
2bd57555-7ffa-4257-8f74-2a9a1e9ed2cc	5002-170	Metolius Bomb Shelter Double Fly	Offering complete foul weather protection when you’re high and committed. The durable main body is made of waterproof, polyurethane-coated fabric with hot-taped seams, The fly has no webbing, so water can’t wick through the fly. Heavy-duty scuff guards protect the wall side of the fly and an easy-install storm pole protects in bad weather. Unique, triangular window lets you check the weather or enjoy the view. The innovative top attachment point gives you an absolutely bombproof attachment to the anchor.Main body is polyurethane-coated 420-denier Oxford fabric.Aircraft quality 6061-T6 aluminum clip-in point incorporates three plates with four through-bolts to securely anchor the fabric and insure a leak-proof seal.Includes a storm pole for more room, increased water repellency, and greater comfort.Tested at altitudes of over 27,000 feet, the window is made of Mountain Hardware's proprietary UVX. Clear, tear-proof and flexible to -66°F.A heavy-duty, Jr. Ballistics abrasion skirt protects the area on the fly between the ledge and the wall.All four corners are double reinforced with Durathane™ haul bag material.Includes an integrated, compression stuff sack.	["Home", "All", "Climbing", "Rock climbing", "Rock hardware", "Aid climbing gear", "Bomb Shelter Double Fly"]	{"Weight": ["2.25kg"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Ideal for": ["Aid climbing"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807418986526/5002170-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8807418986526/5002170-NOC02.jpg"]}	133.13	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5002-170/Bomb-Shelter-Double-Fly
