239ed4c5-c58a-4f72-bf37-29072bee9305	5007-612	North Water PFD Quick Release Sea Link	This short towline attaches, via its D-ring, to any quick-release PFD harness, providing everything you need for a quick tow at sea. For longer tows in open water, where more distance is desired between the boats, extend the line with the a small regulation throw bag.3.6m (12ft.) of sturdy 9.5mm (⅜in.) nylon webbing with a shock absorption system.Paddle carabiner.Built-in flotation.	["Home", "All", "Watersports", "PFDs, helmets and safety equipment", "Boat safety equipment", "PFD Quick Release Sea Link"]	{"Weight": ["550g"], "Made in": ["Canada"], "Ideal for": ["Kayak touring"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818042765342/5007612-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818042765342/5007612-NOC02.jpg"]}	180.67	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5007-612/PFD-Quick-Release-Sea-Link
3ab7b63c-c05e-4bf1-844b-9971d6ad51bf	4004-627	North Water Paddle Leash	Carrying out rescues, snapping photos, taking a snack break, or adjusting your seat or foot pedals: there a lot of reasons you might want both hands free while at sea in a touring kayak. This leash lets you set your paddle down without it getting away. A hook-and-loop band wraps around the paddle shaft. At the other end, a clip hook attaches to deck webbing or D-rings. Note: Not recommended for whitewater kayaking due to the risk of entanglement.Bungi stretches to allow strokes and contracts to minimize tangling.	["Home", "All", "Watersports", "PFDs, helmets and safety equipment", "Boat safety equipment", "Paddle Leash"]	{"Weight": ["40g"], "Made in": ["Canada"], "Ideal for": ["Kayaking"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8817993646110/4004627-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8817993646110/4004627-NOC02.jpg"]}	665.75	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/4004-627/Paddle-Leash
4dff1ae1-bd74-4550-8247-61c0425340ad	4004-626	North Water Vinyl-Tec 2000 Adhesive	An industrial-strength adhesive that creates a strong chemical bond. Use it to attach vinyl-patched D-rings or anchors to Kevlar®, fibreglass, Royalex®, R-light (1996 and newer) boats. You can also use it to repair vinyl float bags.100 ml.Note: important to follow directions for a good bond.	["Home", "All", "Watersports", "Kayaking", "Boat repair", "Vinyl-Tec 2000 Adhesive"]	{"Weight": ["150g"], "Made in": ["Canada"], "Ideal for": ["Canoeing", "Paddleboarding"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818076975134/4004626-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818076975134/4004626-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818076975134/4004626-NOC02.jpg", "https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8818076975134/4004626-NOC02.jpg"]}	1026.26	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/4004-626/Vinyl-Tec-2000-Adhesive
