55116dc3-7eb1-426d-9b8b-049b3f70fd6a	5016-937	Peterson Last Child in the Woods	Nature-deficit disorder isn’t a medical condition – it’s a description of the human costs of being alienated from nature. There are solutions, though, and they’re right in our own backyards. The author brings together research that shows how exposing children to nature is essential for healthy physical, emotional, and spiritual development. Parents have the power to ensure their kids won’t be the last child in the woods, and this book is a step toward reuniting children with nature.	["Home", "All", "Travel gear", "Books and maps", "Training guides and instructional books", "Last Child in the Woods"]	{"ISBN": ["9781565126053"], "Pages": ["391"], "Author": ["Richard Louv"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Language": ["English"], "Ideal for": ["Camping and hiking"], "Published": ["2008"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815716597790/5016937-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815716597790/5016937-NOC02.jpg"]}	132.16	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5016-937/Last-Child-in-the-Woods
