c61c624a-3404-4849-abf8-5e0cc65c01d8	5020-654	West Kootenay Rock Guide	The West Kootenay region in south-central BC is dotted with quaint heritage towns where the locals revere big lines, backcountry touring, and steep mountain biking. The granite may be bigger and more established in Squamish, but the weather is drier in the Kootenays and the climbing scene is budding. This guide covers over 400 climbs from classic alpine routes to lakeside sport crags.	["Home", "All", "Travel gear", "Books and maps", "Guidebooks", "West Kootenay Rock Guide"]	{"ISBN": ["9780981262208"], "Pages": ["162"], "Author": ["Aaron Kristianson, Vince Hempsall"], "Made in": ["Canada"], "Language": ["English"], "Ideal for": ["Rock climbing", "Alpine climbing and mountaineering"], "Published": ["2009"], "Regionality": ["British Columbia"]}	{"low": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815602991134/5020654-NOC02.jpg?w=600&h=600&auto=format&q=60&fit=fill&bg=FFF"], "high": ["https://cdn.mec.ca/medias/sys_master/high-res/high-res/8815602991134/5020654-NOC02.jpg"]}	84.79	https://www.mec.ca/en/product/5020-654/West-Kootenay-Rock-Guide
1f6a8468-5d72-47c1-b693-0f505ce01d98	5002-366	Western Mountaineering Antelope Gore Windstopper -15C Down Sleeping - Unisex	If you are travelling in high alpine environments in “spring”, it’s best to leave nothing to chance. Enter the Antelope. This 3-season bag is light, compressible, and extremely weather resistant. Insulated with 26 ounces of high lofting goose down, it will keep you warm through three seasons and well into the fourth. A full 3-D down filled Super Collar and a robust draft tube trap the warm air you worked so hard to produce. The narrow, but not tight, profile (62in. across the shoulder) makes the bag compact and quick to heat. It is constructed with no side-block baffles so you can distribute the down depending on the temperature. The 5.25in. baffles offer excellent down control. All in all this is one of the most substantial 3-season bags available today.Shell, collar, and draft tube are GORE™ WINDSTOPPER® 830 fabric, which is light and compressible.Lining is made of 20-denier plain weave nylon.Insulated with goose down.Locking #5 YKK zipper.When ordering please specify left or right zip. It is easier to reach across your body and zip up on the opposite side – left zip if you are right-handed and right zip if you are left-handed.	["Home", "All", "Camping and hiking", "Sleeping bags, sleeping pads, quilts and pillows", "Sleeping bags", "Antelope Gore Windstopper -15C Down Sleeping"]	{"Shape": ["Mummy"], "Length": ["Small fits to 5' 6\\" (168 cm)", "Regular fits to 6' 0\\" (183 cm)", "Long fits to 6' 6\\" (198 cm)"], "Weight": ["1.275kg"], "Made in": ["USA"], "Seasons": ["Winter (-15°C to -40°C)"], "Hip girth": ["135cm"], "Ideal for": ["Winter and expedition camping", "Backpacking"], "Foot girth": ["99cm"], "Insulation": ["850+ fill-power goose down"], "Technology": ["GORE-TEX Windstopper"], "Face fabric": ["30-denier nylon"], "Packed size": ["20 x 46cm"], "Temperature": ["-15°C"], "Construction": ["Baffle"], "Lining/backer": ["20-denier nylon"], 